In medium skillet, saute onion and red peppers in 1 tablespoon vinaigrette until crisp tender, about 6 minutes. Season with 2 teaspoons Morton(R) Kosher Salt; keep warm. Cook pasta according to package directions with remaining 1 teaspoon Morton(R) Kosher Salt; drain. Thoroughly toss hot pasta with spinach, pepper onion mixture, remaining vinaigrette and Parmesan cheese. Serve immediately with garlic breadsticks.